ğŸŒ What Is an IP Address?
An IP (Internet Protocol) address is a unique numerical identifier assigned to every device connected to a network.

ğŸ“¦ IPv4 Structure
An IPv4 address is 32 bits, divided into 4 octets (8 bits each)
â†’ Each number (0â€“255) is 8 bits.
Exponent (n)	Expression	Result
